        <h3>Step 1: Prepare Your Workspace</h3>
        <p>Ensure a clean, static-free environment. Gather all tools, including a screwdriver and anti-static wrist strap.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 2: Install the CPU</h3>
        <p>Gently place the CPU into the motherboard socket, aligning the triangle indicators.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 3: Attach CPU Cooler</h3>
        <p>Secure the cooler over the CPU and connect it to the motherboard fan header.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 4: Install RAM</h3>
        <p>Insert RAM sticks into the DIMM slots, ensuring they click into place.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 5: Install Storage</h3>
        <p>Secure SSDs/HDDs into their respective slots and connect them to the motherboard.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 6: Install GPU</h3>
        <p>Insert the GPU into the PCIe slot and secure it with screws.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 7: Connect PSU</h3>
        <p>Attach power cables to all components and motherboard headers.</p>
        
        <h3>Step 8: Cable Management</h3>
        <p>Organize cables for proper airflow and aesthetics.</p>
        
        <h2 id="tips">Additional Tips</h2>
        <p>1. Double-check all connections before powering on.</p>
        <p>2. Update BIOS for compatibility.</p>
        <p>3. Install necessary drivers after booting up.</p>
